text.div:
Expansion performed internally based on codesystem Status Codes Values v2.0.0 (CodeSystem)

This value set contains 6 concepts

CodeSystemDisplay (en-US)Definition
  manualCauseOfDeathCodinghttp://cdc.gov/nchs/nvss/fhir/vital-records-messaging/CodeSystem/VRM-Status-csManual Cause of Death Coding

The death record has been sent for manual cause of death coding.

  manualDemographicCodinghttp://cdc.gov/nchs/nvss/fhir/vital-records-messaging/CodeSystem/VRM-Status-csManual Demographic Coding

The death record has been sent for manual demographic (race/ethnicity) coding.

  noCodingNeeded_Duplicatehttp://cdc.gov/nchs/nvss/fhir/vital-records-messaging/CodeSystem/VRM-Status-csNo Coding Needed - Duplicate

The death record is a duplicate of a previously submitted record, no coding will be performed.

  manualCodingCanceled_Updatehttp://cdc.gov/nchs/nvss/fhir/vital-records-messaging/CodeSystem/VRM-Status-csManual Coding Canceled - Update

An update has been submitted for a death record that is queued for manual coding. The manual coding has been canceled for the original record.

  manualCodingCanceled_Voidhttp://cdc.gov/nchs/nvss/fhir/vital-records-messaging/CodeSystem/VRM-Status-csManual Coding Canceled - Void

A void request has been received for a death record that is queued for manual coding. The manual coding has been canceled for the original record.

  nonCodeablehttp://cdc.gov/nchs/nvss/fhir/vital-records-messaging/CodeSystem/VRM-Status-csNon Codeable

The fetal death record does not meet the criteria for fetal cause of death coding.
